claim.claim-text:
1. A method to support repairable servowriting, comprising:
calculating a first set of wedge offset reduction field (WORF) and/or position error signal (PES) information for one or more servo tracks on a surface of a rotating medium;
comparing the first set of WORF and/or PES information for the one or more servo tracks with a pre-detennined threshold;
repairing a servo burst and/or a boundary of the servo burst on the one or more servo tracks via a read and/or write element of a read/write head if the WORF and/or PES information exceeds the threshold, the repairing including
writing a new servo burst and subsequently trimming the new servo burst; and
repairing a servo burst damaged by the new servo burst;

calculating a second set of WORF and/or PES information for the one or more servo tracks; and
storing the second set of WORF and/or PES information for retrieval during servowriting.

2. A method to support repairable servowriting, comprising:
calculating wedge offset reduction field (WORF) and/or position error signal (PES) information for one or more servo tracks on a surface of a rotating medium;
comparing the WORF and/or PES information for the one or more servo tracks with a pre-determined threshold;
repairing a servo burst and/or a boundary of the servo burst on the one or more servo tracks via a read and/or write element of a read/write head if the WORF and/or PES information exceeds the threshold; and
writing the WORF and/or PES information on the one or more servo tracks.

3. A system to support repairable servowriting, comprising:
a rotatable medium including at least one surface having a plurality of servo tracks operable to store one or more servo bursts;
a read/write head including a read and/or write element operable to servowrite the servo tracks; and
one or more controllers operable to:
rotate the rotatable medium and position the read/write head relative to the rotatable medium;
calculate a first set of wedge offset reduction field (WORF) and/or position error signal (PES) information for one or more servo tracks on a surface of a rotating medium;
compare the first set of WORF and/or PES information for the one or more servo tracks with a pre-determnined threshold; and
repair a servo burst and/or a boundary of the servo burst on the one or more servo tracks via a read and/or write element of a read/write head if the WORF and/or PES information exceeds the threshold, the repair including writing a new servo burst and subsequently trimming the new servo burst and repairing a servo burst damaged by the new servo burst;
calculate a second set of WORF and/or PES information for the one or more servo tracks; and
store the second set of WORF and/or PES information for retrieval during servowriting.

6. A system to support repairable servowriting, comprising:
a rotatable medium including at least one surface having a plurality of servo tracks operable to store one or more servo bursts;
a read/write head including a read and/or write element operable to servowrite the servo tracks; and
one or more controllers operable to:
rotate the rotatable medium and position the read/write head relative to the rotatable medium;
calculate wedge offset reduction field (WORF) and/or position error signal (PES) information for one or more servo tracks on a surface of a rotating medium;
compare the WORF and/or PES information for the one or more servo tracks with a pre-determined threshold;
repair a servo burst and/or a boundary of the servo burst on the one or more servo tracks via a read and/or write element of a read/write head if the WORF and/or PES information exceeds the threshold; and
write the WORF and/or PES information on the one or more servo tracks.
